The paper is about improvements to the YOLO object detection algorithm, which is a popular computer vision technique. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the training of a new neural network, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions accuracy improvements, which is a common topic in the field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a Titan X GPU for testing suggests a focus on hardware optimization, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the speed of the algorithm, which is relevant to the field of cs.MM (Multimedia).
